{
  "texts": [
    "Since the data size is large (> 30), normality was assumed (Gravetter & Wallnau, 2011).",
    "Levene's test results showed homogeneity of variances across profiles (all p values > 0.15).",
    "According to one-way ANOVA results, there was a significant difference in post-test scores across the different AI interaction profiles, F (4, 141) = 3.36, p =.012.",
    "The effect size was large, η²= 0.87.",
    "Post-hoc comparisons using the Tukey HSD test revealed that AI-Assisted Code Refiners had significantly higher scores than AI-Reliant Code Generator & Refiners (p =.010)."
  ]
}